 {"id":"bd-38hvb","title":"[TUI-E2E] End-to-end tests for TUI features with tmux automation","description":"## Problem

TUI-TEST (bd-hz7fx) has 16 unit tests that verify state transitions, but no E2E tests that exercise the actual TUI through terminal interaction. Unit tests test the logic; E2E tests test the real user experience.

## Solution: tmux-Based E2E Tests

### E2E Script 1: Scoped Model Cycling
```bash
# Script: test_e2e_scoped_model_cycling.sh
# Verifies: /scoped-models + Ctrl+P cycling through actual TUI
#
# 1. Launch pi in tmux session with test config
# 2. Send "/scoped-models claude*"
# 3. Verify output shows matched models
# 4. Send Ctrl+P multiple times
# 5. Capture model indicator from status bar after each press
# 6. Verify only claude-* models appear in cycle
# 7. Send "/scoped-models clear"
# 8. Send Ctrl+P
# 9. Verify all models now cycle
#
# JSONL events:
# {"schema":"pi.test.tui_e2e.v1","event":"scoped_models_set","data":{"pattern":"claude*","matched_count":5}}
# {"schema":"pi.test.tui_e2e.v1","event":"ctrl_p_pressed","data":{"cycle":1,"model":"claude-3-haiku"}}
# {"schema":"pi.test.tui_e2e.v1","event":"ctrl_p_pressed","data":{"cycle":2,"model":"claude-3-sonnet"}}
# {"schema":"pi.test.tui_e2e.v1","event":"scope_cleared","data":{"previous_pattern":"claude*"}}
```

### E2E Script 2: Share Command
```bash
# Script: test_e2e_share_command.sh
# Verifies: /share generates gist with correct metadata
#
# 1. Launch pi, send a test prompt, wait for response
# 2. Send "/share"
# 3. Capture output (gist URL or error)
# 4. Verify gist was created (mock gh or check output format)
# 5. Send "/share public"
# 6. Verify public gist creation
#
# JSONL events:
# {"schema":"pi.test.tui_e2e.v1","event":"share_initiated","data":{"privacy":"private"}}
# {"schema":"pi.test.tui_e2e.v1","event":"share_completed","data":{"url":"https://gist.github.com/..."}}
```

### E2E Script 3: Pattern Validation Errors
```bash
# Script: test_e2e_pattern_validation.sh
# Verifies: /scoped-models with invalid patterns shows clear errors
#
# 1. Send "/scoped-models [invalid"
# 2. Verify error message about unclosed bracket
# 3. Send "/scoped-models nonexistent-provider-*"
# 4. Verify warning about zero matches
#
# JSONL events:
# {"schema":"pi.test.tui_e2e.v1","event":"invalid_pattern","data":{"pattern":"[invalid","error":"unclosed bracket"}}
# {"schema":"pi.test.tui_e2e.v1","event":"no_matches","data":{"pattern":"nonexistent-provider-*","matched":0}}
```

### E2E Script 4: Missing gh CLI Error Handling
```bash
# Script: test_e2e_share_no_gh.sh
# Verifies: /share without gh CLI shows install instructions
#
# 1. Launch pi with PATH that excludes gh
# 2. Send "/share"
# 3. Verify error message contains installation URL
#
# JSONL events:
# {"schema":"pi.test.tui_e2e.v1","event":"share_failed","data":{"reason":"gh_not_found","message_contains":"cli.github.com"}}
```

